73
00:02:59,360 --> 00:03:00,190
I'm a bit worried.

74
00:03:01,360 --> 00:03:02,190
Don't worry about it.

75
00:03:02,190 --> 00:03:03,800
It's just
a minimally invasive procedure.

76
00:03:04,120 --> 00:03:05,560
But what if something goes wrong?

77
00:03:05,750 --> 00:03:06,560
It won't.

78
00:03:06,960 --> 00:03:08,030
How could we be that unlucky?

79
00:03:10,840 --> 00:03:12,710
Haven't I always been unlucky?

80
00:03:21,750 --> 00:03:22,190
Xiaozhou.

81
00:03:23,080 --> 00:03:23,680
If...

82
00:03:25,240 --> 00:03:28,150
I mean if the surgery really fails,

83
00:03:29,840 --> 00:03:30,800
can you handle it?

84
00:03:33,800 --> 00:03:34,310
I...

85
00:03:36,870 --> 00:03:38,240
No matter how hard it gets,
I'll have you.

86
00:03:39,590 --> 00:03:39,960
Right?

87
00:03:50,240 --> 00:03:51,030
What did you want to say?

88
00:03:54,840 --> 00:03:55,400
Nothing.

89
00:03:55,960 --> 00:03:56,870
I just wanted...

90
00:03:57,750 --> 00:03:58,960
I just wanted to comfort you.

91
00:04:00,910 --> 00:04:01,870
I'm fine, don't worry.

92
00:04:06,750 --> 00:04:09,150
I still need to revise a paper tonight.

93
00:04:09,470 --> 00:04:10,560
Let's not take too long.

94
00:04:11,080 --> 00:04:12,120
Okay, let's hurry.

95
00:04:12,240 --> 00:04:12,560
Here.

96
00:04:12,560 --> 00:04:12,870
Okay.

97
00:04:13,590 --> 00:04:14,080
I'll walk you back.

98
00:04:15,680 --> 00:04:16,120
Shrimp.

99
00:04:17,800 --> 00:04:18,390
Is it cold already?

100
00:04:21,240 --> 00:04:21,680
Daer?

101
00:04:22,310 --> 00:04:23,750
Tell me about your studies.

102
00:04:25,070 --> 00:04:26,040
It's just so-so.

103
00:04:27,720 --> 00:04:28,270
Modesty.

104
00:04:28,270 --> 00:04:29,510
Let me tell you, this kid is smart.

105
00:04:29,510 --> 00:04:30,480
You're definitely doing well.

106
00:04:30,480 --> 00:04:31,560
Uncle, Auntie.

107
00:04:31,870 --> 00:04:32,750
What brings you here?

108
00:04:33,510 --> 00:04:34,920
Mom! You're finally back!

109
00:04:35,000 --> 00:04:35,630
Back from work?

110
00:04:36,630 --> 00:04:37,360
Hello, Manli.

111
00:04:37,720 --> 00:04:38,630
We came to see you.

112
00:04:39,430 --> 00:04:40,600
Get those things out.

113
00:04:42,560 --> 00:04:43,000
Manli dear.

114
00:04:43,390 --> 00:04:45,120
We know you lack nothing here.

115
00:04:45,310 --> 00:04:46,800
So I just brought you some

116
00:04:47,120 --> 00:04:48,750
spring onions, ginger and such.

117
00:04:49,240 --> 00:04:49,950
Hope you don't mind.

118
00:04:50,390 --> 00:04:51,630
These things are good.

119
00:04:51,950 --> 00:04:52,830
Completely natural.

120
00:04:52,920 --> 00:04:54,360
You can't buy these here with money.

121
00:04:54,680 --> 00:04:54,920
Here.

122
00:04:54,950 --> 00:04:56,240
- Where should I put these? - Thanks.

123
00:04:56,270 --> 00:04:56,680
That's alright.

124
00:04:56,680 --> 00:04:57,120
In the kitchen.

125
00:04:57,120 --> 00:04:57,950
- Let me... - Daer.

126
00:04:57,950 --> 00:04:58,480
I'll do it.

127
00:04:59,830 --> 00:05:00,240
It's fine.

128
00:05:00,830 --> 00:05:02,600
Look, the kid's grown into a young man.

129
00:05:02,600 --> 00:05:03,310
He's all grown up.

130
00:05:03,950 --> 00:05:05,270
Green stuff, good stuff.

131
00:05:08,270 --> 00:05:08,920
Why didn't you call

132
00:05:09,000 --> 00:05:11,680
ahead before you came?

133
00:05:12,120 --> 00:05:13,430
What's there to say? We're family.

134
00:05:13,750 --> 00:05:14,480
We're all family here.

135
00:05:14,800 --> 00:05:16,120
Isn't it just like coming home?

136
00:05:17,070 --> 00:05:17,680
Exactly.

137
00:05:21,920 --> 00:05:22,870
Did you come for something?

138
00:05:23,620 --> 00:05:24,060
Right.

139
00:05:25,390 --> 00:05:25,830
Here.

140
00:05:30,360 --> 00:05:30,950
Well...

141
00:05:32,390 --> 00:05:33,390
A few months ago,

142
00:05:33,870 --> 00:05:34,630
your uncle

143
00:05:34,830 --> 00:05:35,920
had heart troubles.

144
00:05:36,160 --> 00:05:38,430
So we went to the county hospital

145
00:05:38,430 --> 00:05:39,120
for checkups.

146
00:05:39,750 --> 00:05:41,600
But they said their facility
was too small

147
00:05:41,830 --> 00:05:43,560
and referred us to the city hospital.

148
00:05:43,870 --> 00:05:45,600
Then the city sent us to the provincial one.

149
00:05:46,390 --> 00:05:48,120
The doctors at the big provincial hospital said

150
00:05:48,680 --> 00:05:49,270
that he

151
00:05:49,750 --> 00:05:50,680
has this condition...

152
00:05:50,680 --> 00:05:52,950
something about a heart valve not...
not closing right.

153
00:05:53,720 --> 00:05:54,560
He needs surgery.

154
00:05:55,560 --> 00:05:57,070
Pretty scary the way they explained it.

155
00:05:58,560 --> 00:06:00,750
We've been thinking it over

156
00:06:01,310 --> 00:06:03,070
and figured if he needs surgery,

157
00:06:03,600 --> 00:06:05,040
he'd better go to a major city.

158
00:06:05,720 --> 00:06:08,560
First, big-city doctors
are more skilled,

159
00:06:08,720 --> 00:06:09,040
right?

160
00:06:09,190 --> 00:06:10,680
We'd feel safer about the operation.

161
00:06:11,950 --> 00:06:12,510
Second...

162
00:06:12,870 --> 00:06:13,360
Manli...

163
00:06:13,560 --> 00:06:15,070
Didn't you buy that health insurance

164
00:06:15,390 --> 00:06:16,390
for your uncle?

165
00:06:16,510 --> 00:06:16,830
Right?

166
00:06:17,430 --> 00:06:19,360
We thought it'd be easier to file claims.

167
00:06:19,360 --> 00:06:21,070
So that's why we came to you.

168
00:06:24,870 --> 00:06:26,680
Does Zhiyuan know you're here?

169
00:06:27,680 --> 00:06:30,000
We just left
the provincial hospital this morning.

170
00:06:30,000 --> 00:06:31,390
We went straight to the train station.

171
00:06:31,630 --> 00:06:32,950
Didn't have time to call him.

172
00:06:33,510 --> 00:06:33,870
You see.

173
00:06:34,120 --> 00:06:35,560
After getting off the train, your uncle

174
00:06:35,870 --> 00:06:37,430
tried calling Zhiyuan,

175
00:06:37,430 --> 00:06:40,240
but his phone was turned off.

176
00:06:40,270 --> 00:06:41,040
We couldn't reach him.

177
00:06:41,600 --> 00:06:42,390
He's busy, right?

178
00:06:43,160 --> 00:06:43,870
But it's okay.

179
00:06:44,830 --> 00:06:45,310
Anyway,

180
00:06:45,830 --> 00:06:46,720
let him be busy.

181
00:06:47,000 --> 00:06:48,390
We've got you for this matter.

182
00:06:48,560 --> 00:06:49,160
Right, Manli?

183
00:06:49,160 --> 00:06:50,560
It's the same.

184
00:06:52,920 --> 00:06:55,070
I need to tell you something.

185
00:06:58,390 --> 00:06:59,310
Two months ago,

186
00:06:59,920 --> 00:07:01,630
Zhiyuan and I separated.

187
00:07:04,940 --> 00:07:05,420
Huh?

188
00:07:11,920 --> 00:07:13,120
Hello, I'd like to check in.

189
00:07:18,510 --> 00:07:20,430
This hotel isn't as good as last time's.

190
00:07:22,680 --> 00:07:24,310
Even after breaking up,
she still helps us.

191
00:07:24,920 --> 00:07:25,870
What a good person.

192
00:07:37,560 --> 00:07:38,070
Hello.

193
00:07:38,190 --> 00:07:40,000
The number you dialed is powered off.

194
00:07:43,310 --> 00:07:44,560
Zhiyuan's phone is turned off.

195
00:07:44,630 --> 00:07:45,560
Probably ran out of battery.

196
00:07:45,720 --> 00:07:47,120
You can contact him later yourselves.

197
00:07:47,190 --> 00:07:47,510
Alright.

198
00:07:47,870 --> 00:07:50,160
I booked this room for three days.

199
00:07:50,240 --> 00:07:51,000
You can stay here.

200
00:07:53,000 --> 00:07:53,430
Let me do it.

201
00:07:53,680 --> 00:07:54,040
It's okay.

202
00:07:59,950 --> 00:08:00,390
Come on in.

203
00:08:02,750 --> 00:08:03,190
It's time.

204
00:08:03,190 --> 00:08:04,560
I want to watch news!

205
00:08:05,070 --> 00:08:06,040
The TV remote is here.

206
00:08:06,340 --> 00:08:06,940
Right.

207
00:08:10,000 --> 00:08:11,120
This matter can't be delayed.

208
00:08:16,600 --> 00:08:18,160
He still keeps this habit.

209
00:08:18,800 --> 00:08:19,070
Yes.

210
00:08:19,070 --> 00:08:20,270
Takes notes while watching news.

211
00:08:21,430 --> 00:08:22,160
Don't mind him, come.

212
00:08:22,750 --> 00:08:23,600
Sit here.

213
00:08:24,000 --> 00:08:25,040
Sit down and rest for a while.

214
00:08:26,630 --> 00:08:27,600
Tell me.

215
00:08:28,600 --> 00:08:30,360
What happened between you and Zhiyuan?

216
00:08:31,390 --> 00:08:32,320
During New Year's,

217
00:08:32,320 --> 00:08:33,600
you two even came home together.

218
00:08:33,870 --> 00:08:35,840
How could you break up so suddenly?

219
00:08:36,510 --> 00:08:37,320
We're incompatible.

220
00:08:39,150 --> 00:08:40,550
You've been together for so many years.

221
00:08:40,550 --> 00:08:41,630
You're incompatible now?

222
00:08:42,600 --> 00:08:43,550
You must have argued.

223
00:08:44,670 --> 00:08:45,720
Said things in the heat of the moment?

224
00:08:47,320 --> 00:08:47,840
Manli...

225
00:08:48,510 --> 00:08:50,240
When two people live together,

226
00:08:50,960 --> 00:08:52,550
there are bound to be bumps.

227
00:08:52,630 --> 00:08:53,000
Right?

228
00:08:53,200 --> 00:08:53,670
Look.

229
00:08:54,120 --> 00:08:55,030
My husband and I

230
00:08:55,030 --> 00:08:56,550
have been together almost a lifetime,

231
00:08:56,750 --> 00:08:58,030
and we still argue.

232
00:08:58,720 --> 00:08:59,600
It's normal.

233
00:08:59,910 --> 00:09:01,240
Not worth splitting up.

234
00:09:01,240 --> 00:09:02,150
You call those arguments?

235
00:09:02,720 --> 00:09:03,720
That's me letting you win!

236
00:09:04,240 --> 00:09:05,080
I can't be bothered.

237
00:09:05,670 --> 00:09:06,150
Alright.

238
00:09:06,510 --> 00:09:07,720
You're already out of breath.

239
00:09:07,870 --> 00:09:08,600
Save your energy.

240
00:09:10,510 --> 00:09:10,960
Manli.

241
00:09:11,630 --> 00:09:12,030
Don't worry.

242
00:09:13,120 --> 00:09:14,440
When I see Zhiyuan later,

243
00:09:14,670 --> 00:09:15,720
I'll give him a good talking-to.

244
00:09:16,790 --> 00:09:18,360
Can families just split like that?

245
00:09:21,910 --> 00:09:23,240
What happened between him and me

246
00:09:23,360 --> 00:09:25,390
are quite complicated.

247
00:09:26,670 --> 00:09:27,790
Ask him yourself later.

248
00:09:29,240 --> 00:09:29,720
See?

249
00:09:30,380 --> 00:09:30,980
Hey!

250
00:09:31,630 --> 00:09:33,120
Your nephew's been a bully again!

251
00:09:35,550 --> 00:09:36,000
Manli.

252
00:09:36,840 --> 00:09:37,750
All these years

253
00:09:37,960 --> 00:09:39,390
How you've treated Zhiyuan

254
00:09:40,080 --> 00:09:41,480
and the Dings,

255
00:09:41,790 --> 00:09:43,550
I've seen it all and remember.

256
00:09:44,150 --> 00:09:45,270
It must be his fault.

257
00:09:45,720 --> 00:09:47,030
He must have upset you.

258
00:09:47,670 --> 00:09:48,360
I'll scold him.

259
00:09:48,750 --> 00:09:49,750
I have your back.

260
00:09:51,440 --> 00:09:52,200
It's getting late.

261
00:09:52,440 --> 00:09:53,480
You should rest early.

262
00:09:53,550 --> 00:09:54,240
I'll head back now.

263
00:09:54,630 --> 00:09:55,320
Alright.

264
00:09:57,000 --> 00:09:57,440
I'm off.

265
00:09:58,390 --> 00:09:59,030
Get some rest.

266
00:09:59,870 --> 00:10:00,240
Got it!

267
00:10:00,360 --> 00:10:01,200
Take care, Manli.

268
00:10:06,670 --> 00:10:07,960
Your uncle and aunt came for treatment.

269
00:10:07,960 --> 00:10:09,000
They couldn't reach you.

270
00:10:09,200 --> 00:10:10,510
I've already arranged their stay.

271
00:10:10,630 --> 00:10:11,840
I'll send you the address later.

272
00:10:14,390 --> 00:10:14,960
Mr. Chen,

273
00:10:15,440 --> 00:10:17,270
I've customized this plan for your family.

274
00:10:17,270 --> 00:10:17,630
Look.

275
00:10:18,840 --> 00:10:19,870
Education annuity.

276
00:10:20,600 --> 00:10:22,720
Pension, critical illness and medical insurance.

277
00:10:27,510 --> 00:10:28,840
Wait, Ms. Hu.

278
00:10:29,510 --> 00:10:29,790
Wait.

279
00:10:30,240 --> 00:10:32,440
Why isn't my mother included in the

280
00:10:32,670 --> 00:10:33,440
medical insurance?

281
00:10:34,550 --> 00:10:36,270
She's almost eighty.

282
00:10:36,720 --> 00:10:37,550
Regular medical insurance

283
00:10:37,550 --> 00:10:39,000
doesn't cover people over sixty.

284
00:10:40,030 --> 00:10:40,960
What are saying?

285
00:10:42,870 --> 00:10:44,870
Those who need insurance
can't get insured?

286
00:10:45,550 --> 00:10:46,960
You keep pushing people who don't need

287
00:10:47,320 --> 00:10:48,600
insurance to buy it anyway.

288
00:10:49,790 --> 00:10:51,320
Mr. Chen, that's not what I meant.

289
00:10:51,390 --> 00:10:52,320
Then what do you mean?

290
00:10:53,270 --> 00:10:53,670
Right?

291
00:10:54,720 --> 00:10:56,080
Ms. Hu, you're a good person.

292
00:10:56,720 --> 00:10:57,790
But your company

293
00:10:58,030 --> 00:10:59,790
only wants risk-free profits.

